http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/KGH-to-get-more-nurses-soon/article13988257.ece

Health Minister Kamineni Srinivasa Rao has announced that 1,000 vacant posts of nurse would be filled in the State and some of them would be allocated to King George Hospital in the city.The Minister inaugurated a Sick New Born Care Unit, set up at a cost of Rs.38 lakh, at KGH on Thursday.Admitting that there was acute shortage of nurses in the hospital, he said that they would be posted soon.Later, he inspected the hospital.MP K. Haribabu, MLA Vasupalli Ganesh Kumar, and KGH Superintendent D. Madhusudhana Babu were present.